1
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,433
The crew is here.

2
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,267
We could start and finish early.

3
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,733
Are you sure
that's what you will wear

4
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,533
on the first day of your
community service?

5
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,467
Never miss an opportunity
to make a good impression.

6
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,800
And to look beautiful,
of course.

7
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:35,667
And like what Italians say, La
Bella Figura (Fine appearance).

8
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:39,133
She and Lara were there
near our table,

9
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:41,667
for sure they copied
our proposal.

10
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:45,433
So are you accusing me
of copying your proposal?

11
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,833
Stop acting as if you're
the most beautiful

12
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:51,533
and intelligent person,
because clearly it's not you.

13
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:56,267
- Tiff!
- Let go of me!

14
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:59,300
So this is our coconut
processing plant.

15
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:01,500
It's beautiful here.

16
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:03,067
My outfit is perfect
for this place.

17
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,400
It's beautiful.

18
00:01:04,467 --> 00:01:06,033
Oh, oh my God.

19
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,000
This is cute. You can take
a picture of me here.

20
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:12,600
It's for my OOTD like pushing,
working hard.

21
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:15,033
Like this or this...

22
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:18,967
Your community service today
is copra processing.

23
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:19,900
What?
Nothing will happen to you
there.

24
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:21,900
There's no force.
You should sit like this.

25
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,300
You should fix your position.

26
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:27,600
Like this.

27
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:28,967
What?

28
00:01:29,033 --> 00:01:30,500
Not like that.

29
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:32,267
Put your leg on the other side.

30
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:33,400
There you go.

31
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,500
Are you torturing me
or punishing me?

32
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:38,867
Sorry, but just because
you will promote Sorsogon,

33
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:41,100
it doesn't mean you will not do
your community service properly.

34
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,467
Of course, you still have
to do that.

35
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:46,933
Now, I prepared some food
so we can eat.

36
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,700
I don't eat rice.

37
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:49,833
So don't.

38
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:50,700
It's really like that.

39
00:01:50,767 --> 00:01:52,133
You want to get thin.

40
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:52,767
Ah...

41
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:53,900
ouch.

42
00:01:53,967 --> 00:01:54,800
Are you okay?

43
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:02,833
I'll press it.

44
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:09,200
Of all the people you've had
a relationship with

45
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:10,700
for the past few years,

46
00:02:10,767 --> 00:02:13,433
you're still looking for Dad
in all of them.

47
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,967
And I'm not saying this to you
to ridicule you or something.

48
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:19,933
But as a concerned daughter,

49
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,933
your happiness is very important
to me.

50
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,900
So how was the first day
of community service?

51
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:26,933
It was nice.

52
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,300
It's a bit hard,
but I felt good.

53
00:02:29,367 --> 00:02:30,633
What made you feel good?

54
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:50,700
Don't you have any story
to tell me?

55
00:02:50,767 --> 00:02:51,800
Story?

56
00:02:51,867 --> 00:02:54,167
Yes, oh jeez.

57
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:56,267
Can't you tell me

58
00:02:56,333 --> 00:03:00,833
about the whole day you spent
with your former sweetheart?

59
00:03:02,133 --> 00:03:03,900
That's work, Grandmother.

60
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:05,033
There's nothing I can do.

61
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,667
I was assigned to be
her probation officer.

62
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:10,933
Hey!
What's with you?

63
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,233
You're here right away?

64
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:17,433
Of course, she can smell
what we are cooking.

65
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,333
That's not what I smell.

66
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:23,300
What I can smell is the rumor
that is going around here.

67
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,867
What's the latest?

68
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:26,833
You are crazy.

69
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:28,000
Nothing, okay?

70
00:03:28,067 --> 00:03:30,133
There's no rumor going around.

71
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,267
Really, Mikoy?

72
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,500
Admit it.

73
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:38,333
Don't expect too much
because there's no update.

74
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,100
I have nothing to tell you.

75
00:03:41,167 --> 00:03:44,967
You haven't even restored
your old friendship?

76
00:03:47,067 --> 00:03:52,500
Grandmother, the Celeste
that you will see today

77
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:56,533
is different from the Celeste
that we knew before.

78
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,200
And with her personality now...

79
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:05,800
I don't think she wants to be
friends with people like us.

80
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:10,567
Grandson, you just can't change
your whole personality.

81
00:04:10,633 --> 00:04:15,400
Sometimes, the real us
is just hidden

82
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:19,067
by the personality that we want
other people to see.

83
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:23,733
Maybe Celeste just forget
her old self

84
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:26,533
and maybe we can remind her
again.

85
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,800
- Hey! Wait, Ma'am.
- No! Don't touch me.

86
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:12,633
Tonito!

87
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,900
Please call him.

88
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:15,767
But, Ma'am...

89
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,167
You're rude. Call Tonito.

90
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,600
- Ma'am...
- Tonito!

91
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,200
Don't touch me.

92
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,667
- Ma'am?
- What's with you?

93
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:26,467
Please, that's enough.

94
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:29,633
Tonito!

95
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,767
- Tonito.
- Ma'am...

96
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:34,833
Sir, I'm sorry.

97
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:38,733
I tried to stop her,
but she insisted.

98
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,833
Prepare the guest room.

99
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:41,033
Okay, yes.

100
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,333
Hi, darling.

101
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,533
This is all your fault.

102
00:05:48,467 --> 00:05:50,733
Aurelia, you should rest here
first.

103
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:53,567
No, no, I don't want your pity.

104
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:56,067
I don't want your pity.

105
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:58,767
I want answers, okay?

106
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,067
Aurelia.

107
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,967
Why her?

108
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:07,833
Why were you able...

109
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,067
to love her?

110
00:06:14,533 --> 00:06:15,733
How about me?

111
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:29,133
Why can't you love me...

112
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,800
the way you love her?

113
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:38,133
You know, funny enough...

114
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,133
all these years...

115
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,667
I convinced myself...

116
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,833
that I don't feel anything
for you...

117
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,533
and I almost succeeded.

118
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,600
I...

119
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:09,367
I felt like I was so over you.

120
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:10,300
But...

121
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,433
you flaunted to everyone...

122
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:23,433
that you will marry that woman.

123
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,100
My heart was broken.

124
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:37,100
I was still hoping...

125
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:40,867
that we will get back together.

126
00:07:44,033 --> 00:07:44,933
Aurelia.

127
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:47,300
Tonito...

128
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:53,933
can we be a couple again?

129
00:07:56,967 --> 00:07:57,867
Please...

130
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,867
take me back.

131
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,300
Please...

132
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,233
give us...

133
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:09,733
another chance.

134
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:39,000
Hey...

135
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,067
there's charcoal on your nose.

136
00:08:58,433 --> 00:08:59,500
I'll press it.

137
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:01,633
Sorry.

138
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:04,467
Good morning, Celeste.

139
00:10:04,533 --> 00:10:05,333
Come on.

140
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:09,300
I already said I don't eat
breakfast.

141
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:10,667
Yeah...

142
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:15,633
fasting, intermittent fasting,
right?

143
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,733
I didn't prepare breakfast.

144
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,633
Your father only drinks coffee
in the morning.

145
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:24,900
And Sebastian is having porridge
early outside.

146
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:27,267
But I prepared food for you.

147
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,900
I don't eat carbs.

148
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:32,200
Yes, I did research last night.

149
00:10:32,267 --> 00:10:34,700
Your diet is a bit complicated.

150
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,767
It has a lot of versions.

151
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:38,033
- There's keto...
- Keto.

152
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:41,367
There's keto, Atkins.

153
00:10:41,433 --> 00:10:43,600
Here I made everything.

154
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:46,067
It's easy to make.

155
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,933
Just choose what you want

156
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
and you can give to others
what you don't want, right?

157
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,233
Here.

158
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:57,400
Here's the other one.

159
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:03,500
It's an inconvenience...

160
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:06,133
but I'll take it.

161
00:11:08,933 --> 00:11:10,100
Have a good day!

162
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:18,733
Are you sure about
what you're doing?

163
00:11:20,733 --> 00:11:25,400
It seems like it's hard to get
rid of the resentment

164
00:11:25,467 --> 00:11:27,367
that was kept for a long time.

165
00:11:27,433 --> 00:11:32,333
Yes, but we can try little
by little.

166
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:36,733
I can't help but think
that it was my fault

167
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:40,133
why your relationship with
your daughter ended like that.

168
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,833
So with my own little way...

169
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:48,900
I can restore even a bit of her
respect for you as her father.

170
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,000
Tiff...

171
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,233
you're lucky.

172
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,367
You weren't kicked out.

173
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:10,000
You used your charm
to the schoolmistress.

174
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:15,800
Well, David, Cynthia is luckier.

175
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,567
That's only what she got
from me.

176
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:21,167
Or she would've lost
all her hair by now.

177
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:25,300
Everyone is talking about
your stepmother, Tiffany.

178
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:27,800
She got some crazy videos
in Sorsogon.

179
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,800
James?

180
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:32,800
Babe...

181
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:38,167
please stop your obsession
with my dad's girlfriend.

182
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:41,167
Didn't I tell you that I don't
want to hear anything about her?

183
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,500
Why are you so stubborn?

184
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,900
Actually, Tiffany, I didn't
search for your stepmother.

185
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:50,133
I was searching for alternative
places for our project.

186
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:52,933
I just found Sorsogon
and there she was.

187
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Yeah, Sorsogon is a good
alternative.

188
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,900
Yeah, they are famous
for Donsol...

189
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,700
you know, the whale sharks.

190
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:03,633
And I think it's easier
to market.

191
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:08,233
Exactly and instead of
using Albay,

192
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:10,000
we can use Sorsogon instead.

193
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:12,267
I have a friend.

194
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:16,367
He told me that there are secret
surfing spots in Sorsogon.

195
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:17,533
That would be nice.

196
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:22,700
And maybe when they stole
your idea of using Albay

197
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:26,833
as a location is actually
a blessing in disguise.

198
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:30,367
It's possible that we can mount
a better event in Sorsogon.

199
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:31,633
What do you think, Tiff?

200
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,000
Well, if you guys are sure...

201
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:40,533
why not?

202
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,100
Then, Sorsogon it is!

203
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,767
David, just relax.

204
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:44,933
You're not in our group.

205
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,533
It is settled then.

206
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:50,000
Sorsogon, here I come.

207
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:55,267
Sorsogon, Donsol, Whale sharks,
Sorsogon.

208
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:56,733
I'm so excited.

209
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:11,533
Grandmother!

210
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,167
Here's the sticky rice.

211
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,300
Grandmother?

212
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:20,600
We Sorsoguenos are really
happy people.

213
00:14:20,667 --> 00:14:22,633
Who wouldn't be happy

214
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:26,767
if you were born in a
paradise-like place?

215
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:32,300
And if delicious food
is served on your table.

216
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,567
Yes.

217
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:36,100
You know, when Mikoy
is still a child,

218
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:38,700
I taught him the secret

219
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:41,567
that my Grandfather and
Grandmother passed on to me.

220
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:46,267
If you want your cooking to
taste good, you should be happy.

221
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:50,767
Oh, just be happy.

222
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,567
I'll make it happier.

223
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:53,867
It's just like this.

224
00:14:53,933 --> 00:14:59,600
Pak, pak, bet!

225
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:00,500
- Oh jeez.
- Like this.

226
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:01,867
Is that okay with you,
Grandmother?

227
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,500
Do you have worms in your body?

228
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:04,467
It's your turn, Grandmother.

229
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:05,833
Do it.

230
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:08,867
Pak, pak, bet!

231
00:15:08,933 --> 00:15:09,633
Stop it.

232
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:12,067
- Come on.
- I don't want to.

233
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:13,533
Come on, just do it once.

234
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,867
- Pak, pak, bet!
- What's with you?

235
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:17,533
- I told you not to force me.
- Pak, pak, bet!

236
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,533
Pak, pak, bet!

237
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,900
One more time, Grandmother.

238
00:15:21,967 --> 00:15:25,533
Pak, pak, bet!

239
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,700
Lower, Grandmother.

240
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:28,933
Pak, pak, bet!

241
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,800
My hips hurt.

242
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:33,933
Are you okay?

243
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:34,900
I'm okay.

244
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,567
If this won't make
our food delicious,

245
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:40,633
I don't know what will.

246
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:41,767
But it'll be happier,

247
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:45,000
Grandmother, if Mikoy
and Celeste are here.

248
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:48,400
Let them have quality time.

249
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:50,200
Is it really quality?

250
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:54,933
Every time I talk to Celeste,
she seems very tired.

251
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:58,433
It doesn't matter if you get
tired of community service

252
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,833
as long as you don't get tired
of loving.

253
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,700
That's it.

254
00:16:03,767 --> 00:16:09,067
Grandmother Ikay, do you think
Mikoy still loves Celeste?

255
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,067
Can I suggest something?

256
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:14,233
What is it?

257
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:17,667
You should eat squash,
so you'll have better eyesight.

258
00:16:17,733 --> 00:16:19,200
Squash?

259
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:20,067
Ah...

260
00:16:20,133 --> 00:16:30,100
Pak, pak, bet!

261
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:39,300
You haven't learned
your lesson?

262
00:16:39,367 --> 00:16:41,433
You have this figura,
figura thing.

263
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,567
Look, you're having
a hard time again.

264
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:45,500
I made a way.

265
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:48,700
What is this?

266
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,633
What is this?
I stepped on something.

267
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:52,433
Something splattered.

268
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,833
- What's this?
- Just wait.

269
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:54,767
Wait.

270
